{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650566","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650566"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:14:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:14:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18412"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18412","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18412"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11130"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77614"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11130","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11130"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18412"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63127"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5295"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25797"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25800"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77614","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77614"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the first-line treatment for Duchenne muscular dystrophy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Satellite cell transplants","Ataluren","Antisense oligonucleotides","Rifampicin","Glucocorticoids"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms suggestive of Duchenne muscular dystrophy, a genetic disorder characterised by progressive muscle degeneration and weakness. \u003Cstrong\u003EGlucocorticoids\u003C/strong\u003E are the first-line treatment for Duchenne muscular dystrophy. They are used to slow the progression of muscle weakness and preserve muscle function. The use of glucocorticoids has been shown to improve muscle strength and function, delay the progression of scoliosis, and prolong ambulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAtaluren\u003C/strong\u003E is a treatment option for patients with Duchenne muscular dystrophy who have a specific nonsense mutation in the dystrophin gene. It is not the first-line treatment for all patients with muscular dystrophy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntisense oligonucleotides\u003C/strong\u003E are used in specific genetic contexts, such as exon skipping therapies for certain mutations in Duchenne muscular dystrophy. They are not the first-line treatment for all patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESatellite cell transplants\u003C/strong\u003E are an experimental approach and are not currently a standard treatment for muscular dystrophy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERifampicin\u003C/strong\u003E is an antibiotic and has no role in the treatment of muscular dystrophy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Glucocorticoids are the first-line treatment for Duchenne muscular dystrophy to slow disease progression.","Glucocorticoids help preserve muscle strength and function in patients with muscular dystrophy.","Other treatments like ataluren and antisense oligonucleotides are used in specific genetic contexts."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Longo, U. G., \u0026 Denaro, V. (Eds.). (2023). Textbook of musculoskeletal disorders. Springer Nature","Hughes, S. H. (2022). The Musculoskeletal System: The Musculoskeletal System-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Frontera WR, Ochala J. Skeletal muscle: a brief review of structure and function. Calcif Tissue Int. 2015 Mar;96(3):183-95. doi: 10.1007/s00223-014-9915-y. Epub 2014 Oct 8. PMID: 25294644","Morrison BM. Neuromuscular Diseases. Semin Neurol. 2016 Oct;36(5):409-418. doi: 10.1055/s-0036-1586263. Epub 2016 Sep 23. PMID: 27704495","Birnkrant DJ, Bushby K, Bann CM, Apkon SD, Blackwell A, Brumbaugh D, Case LE, Clemens PR, Hadjiyannakis S, Pandya S, Street N, Tomezsko J, Wagner KR, Ward LM, Weber DR; DMD Care Considerations Working Group. Diagnosis and management of Duchenne muscular dystrophy, part 1: diagnosis, and neuromuscular, rehabilitation, endocrine, and gastrointestinal and nutritional management. Lancet Neurol. 2018 Mar;17(3):251-267. doi: 10.1016/S1474-4422(18)30024-3. Epub 2018 Feb 3. Erratum in: Lancet Neurol. 2018 Jun;17(6):495. doi: 10.1016/S1474-4422(18)30125-X. PMID: 29395989; PMCID: PMC5869704."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63127"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18412"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63127"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T20:35:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T20:36:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11130"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77614"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedi